               <residence>He was born in <placeName ref="LOC2804Egypt">Egypt.</placeName></residence>
               <floruit when="1348" evidence="internal">He succeeded ʾabuna <persName ref="PRS10200Yaeqob">Yāʿqob</persName>
                  <date>1348</date> who had been expelled 
                  by King <persName ref="PRS8595SayfaAr">Sayfa ʾArʿad</persName> in <date>1344</date>. He was an important metropolitan for the development of Gǝʿǝz literature, 
                  who translated hagiographies, homiles and other works from Arabic into Gǝʿǝz. 
                  Apart from his translation works, he is also credited with one original writing, the          
                  <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1644Homily">Homily on the Deceased</ref>.
               </floruit>
